annotation.TEXT: Now, I could rewind out of that, since that was blatantly unfair (and because the Yoshi greeting message told me that I could), but I'll just keep playing normally instead.
D'oh, I missed!
Fish glitch FTHOI (for the heck of it)!
Okay, I should really just enter the side area before these fish kill me.
And, it appears that there's now a sloped landmass where the first Yoshi block would normally be. Well, maybe I can get Yoshi in the second half of the level.
Gulp!
Hello, and welcome back to Super Tweak World! Now, before I enter Yoshi's Island 2 here, there's a couple things I gotta check out over in these levels on the left... First, Yoshi's Island 1.
To be continued... Yo!
Alright, so if I don't hit this message box to remove the water, I can simply swim over to the key. But, is there anything to the right of the key?
Bah, why did that guy have to dip below the ground there? He screwed up my combo.

So, yeah. It appears that once again, there weren't any changes made to the latter portion of the level. In fact, I think the only changes to this level were within the first few screens (the fake floor, rocks, triple rotating platforms around the clear block, and cheepo generator).
Only 30, but that's just enough to trigger the bonus game!
Oh, geez. Flying cheepos? Well, at least there should be plenty of mushrooms available in this level.
Goal tape average so far: 100 / 3 = 33.333 stars each.
So, things might be getting more interesting in this level.
Lucky stomp there. Sometimes, the game will let you stomp midair enemies (such as super koopas) while you're ascending. (So, why couldn't I stomp a flying cheepo while ascending in the last episode?)

Hmm... Just like with YI1, it doesn't look like there were any changes to the last few screens of the level. In fact, I don't think the second half of this level was ever touched by the waffle doctor.
Thank you, green shell, for shielding me from that super koopa.
Bonus game average so far: 8 / 1 = 8 1-ups each.
What the french toast?!

Hi, Yoshi! I see your message has been changed! ...Um... You misspelled "function". Also, I don't think you should be suggesting the use of emulator tools in-game like this, unless it's a hack that's specifically meant for TAS-ing (like Walljump Mountain).
Alright, I'm outta here. Next, I just want to check out something in Disappearing Tides.
Moon count: 1
Or, I can get lucky and bounce off a fish that happened to be in a good spot there.
Yeah, there's fake floor tiles right there! Um, waffledoctor87, I definitely don't approve of that tweak. That's just plain unfair to the player.
This message is unchanged.
Okay, we've got a mole, and a piranha plant, and... apparently a super koopa generator as well.
Goal tape average so far: 70 / 2 = 35 stars each.
Oh, this message is new! ...Let me guess, you just flipped the "ON" block graphics, right? Well, that's actually fine, and somewhat clever.

Now, I'd normally say "And now, ludicrous speed bonus game." at this point, possibly in another language or in code, but I forgot to speed up the bonus game footage here, so have a normal speed bonus game instead!
However, this hack seems like it's meant to be perfectly playable tool-less, so I don't think I'll be rewinding to rescue Yoshi if he falls into a pit.
Meh, I shouldn't be wasting time with things like that. It makes the video more boring.
...a MOON!!! Yeah, this is the very same moon you'd normally find here in YI1, except that waffledoctor87 provided a way to reach it without using a cape or Yoshi jump!
Nice! I love doing that to that piranha plant!
That's the last Yoshi coin for this level.
Nothing out of the ordinary over here. Also, entering the pipe got rid of the super koopa generator, which is nice.
Demo count: 2
BARF! Well, I'll just hit midpoint before grabbing my reserve flower so that I'll end up with a spare mushroom.
Alright, let's see what's different in YI3!
Nope. The screen stops scrolling there. (Yeah, some of you did mention in the comments last time that there was nothing there, but I just wanted to see for myself.)
I don't know why I'm bothering to collect all of the coins here.
Yep, most of the things in this level are still in their usual spots, like this Yoshi coin up here.
Let's see here...

Fortunately, it looks like the side area functions normally, and hopefully, this'll get rid of the cheepo generator when I return to the main area. Unfortunately, once again, the side area appears to be unchanged.

The vertical checkered platform that's supposed to be here didn't show up. Honestly, I think the cheepo generator should just plain be removed from this level, because it's causing way too many issues with the sprite limit.
Nuts, mistimed my A button press on Yoshi there, but at least I got a few 1-ups from the combo this time!
Demo count: 1
Hmm... Unfortunately, it doesn't look like this bonus room has been changed at all.
...Huh? ...Oh, right. The eating block at the key earlier, which can be triggered with any brown used block object, not just from the invisible coin block underneath them.
That fire flower is new. Normally, there's a yellow ! block there.
Okay, now for Yoshi's Island 2!
Perfect!
So, will YI4 and Iggy's Castle have any interesting tweaks? Find out next time!
Also, let me just check to make sure the midpoint entrance is properly set...
Wheeee!
This message is unchanged.
Alright, now it's time to climb this yellow ! block wall, where I shall find...

The ends of a couple of these platforms are pulling Houdinis as well, and why is there a clear block right here? It doesn't fit well with this sprite tileset, because it looks like the edge of a checkered platform when I hit it.
I'll just speed up some of this footage here...
Okay, first of all, Yoshi's head was missing. Second of all, I fell through the floor! Was the floor really fake, or was I just not paying attention to something?
The sprite limit seems to be limiting the cheepo density. However, that also means that the cheepos could keep other sprites from showing up.
Yes! This doesn't quite make up for the fake floor and the sprite limit screwing over my Yoshi opportunities here, but it's something, at least.
Nuts. I'm pretty sure the sprite limit kept one of those red koopas from spawning.
Yep, already, one of the three rocks here failed to spawn the second time. Also, there might've been more than three rocks that were meant to show up for all I know.
Blaster combo! (9 hits) 3-life combo!
Yep, I figured a Chuck was there. Oh, and here's some "NO" blocks! Aw, too bad I don't have a shell to chuck at that Lava Lotus.
Can I get the platform to appear somehow? Or will I have to resort to making a sprinting jump from the yellow ! blocks to the side area pipe?
This message box seems to be having the same sprite memory visibility issues as Yoshi's head did. Also, the message is unchanged.
...Ugh, speaking of sprites that failed to spawn, Yoshi is a no-show this time, thanks to the sprite limit! Nuts!
I think I'm going to try to clone this flower block.

Also, I never saw any more "NO" blocks besides the three holding up the Lava Lotus near midpoint. That's a bummer. I was hoping for some interesting level tweaks involving them (especially since the message box told me to "Tread with care").
Okay, good. No more cheepos. Let's see if there have been any changes to the second half of the level.
Looks fine to me, although I can hit the bar again, but that's probably a good thing, so that you can get a free embiggening if you're starting there small.
